@node Trapdoor "3.3 Trapdoor"

Article: 11597 of comp.sys.amiga.datacomm
From: Klaus_Seistrup@magneto.bbs.bad.se (Klaus Seistrup)
Subject: Re: AXsh - how do I set it up to run?
Message-ID: <OA92-910-102_17f9225a@piraya.bad.se>
Date: Sat,  6 Mar 93 18:46:56 +0100
Organization: Magnetic Ink, Copenhagen N, Denmark 

  Hello Soeren.

[04-Mar-93: Soeren]

 SBH> I'm trying to get AXsh running, but it seems to fail every time I use
 SBH> the ax-server. So I was wondering, if it's possible to get another
 SBH> program to call axsh, perhaps some kind of trapdoor.

 SBH> Does anyone know of such program, and if so, where would I find it.

I'm spawning AXsh from TrapDoor:

    [TrapDoor.cfg]
    BBSCOMMAND "Execute S:SpawnAXsh.td"

    [SpawnAXsh.td]
    .KEY BAUD/A
    .BRA {
    .KET }

    CD AXSH:
    bin/AXsh <AXAUX:baudbandit.device/0/shared/speed38400 >AXAUX:baudbandit.device/0/shared/speed38400 -log
    BaudCount LOG:BaudCount.idx {BAUD}

'tworks fine. :-)

    /\
   / Kleis
  /____\

@endnode

*****************************************************************************

@node Other "3.4 Other"

@{b}AXsh/AmiExpress selection@{ub}

rc.server:
~~~~~~~~~~
%newshell:
execute <>nil: axsh:etc/remote-startup2

remote-startup2:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
.key NAME/A,NUM/A,SPEED/A
.bra {
.ket }

set devicename {NAME}
set devicenum {NUM}
set speed {SPEED}
newshell <NIL: >NIL: newaux:{NAME}/{NUM}/con/shared/checkcd/useodu from AXsh:etc/remote-startup


remote-startup:
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
stack 20000
AXsh:bin/AXsh -log
endcli

ask "Enter AXsh ? [y/n]"
if warn
  AXsh:bin/AXsh -log
else
  run <>nil: lockserial -A -D $devicename -U $devicenum "express $devicenum $speed"
endif
endcli

@endnode
